<br>
At 63 the two back scarabs could not be singled, so I just took them both on at once. Once the spawns are broken -- only needs to be done once -- it's as easy as gnomish clockwork. If you get bored you can even take the guardian and pick up a Lammy for a twink or something.<br>
<br>
61 pet held up well, esp with the 60 heal. Either 61 air or Epic should be used. Those froglok wizards can hurt once you're hit with malosi and/or tash, so stuns are essential! Host of the Elements comes in handy too for those occasional emergencies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shazar23>Shazar23</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 495<br> <font color=#333333>(1/17/03 3:45:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=48>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cash Options</span><hr size=1> Regarding PoG...<br>
