<br>
1) kite it along the wall until you get enough distance to summon airpet. Worked fine with my 30k horse, just recently got run3 (i know, i know, most 51s have it =/ I'm lazy), both work fine. kite, summon pet, BOV, DS, then chain nuke it down and throw in a renewal (infusion works fine too) occasionally<br>
<br>
sometimes i'd get an add, if i did just kite the add and gate.<br>
<br>
2) easier solution -- run to wall, run all the way down to lake camp spot and camp. you can easily camp before the whorl gets there if you have run3 -- it's slow as junk. think a glorified spec with a max hit of 150 something.<br>
<br>
very, very rarely you will get a sowed whirl, the ONLY time that happened to me was when i aggro whorl and then got a horsee add (druid horse) that sowed the whorl, which made it tough to kite far enough away to summon pet. ended up tanking it long enough to annul and then kiting for pet.<br>
<br>
<br>
PoG is completely gimp as long as you stay on the easier side of the zone. hell, i can tank half this stuff if my pet gets in trouble, and i'm 62 with decent gear but not uber crap.<br>
<br>
if i get an add, chain transons renewal and transons infusion on pet with DS, throwing in a nuke if you get ahead on healing. largely depending on what type the add is you may or may not be able to kill it...<br>
<br>
i find mage duos work great here. even better is mage/mage/shaman or enc. you can own almost the entire zone sans ali and tuna. <br>
<br>
really, guys, you've let VI get you into the mindset that add without pet instantly means you can't handle it. with run3 i can kite a lot of non-summoning stuff, even without snare. takes a lot of mana, but doable.<br>
<br>
you're welcome to send me tells if you have any questions about PoG -- it's my favorite cash farm and i'm always the only person there unless i bring friends. made 1.7k in gems and 2 bds (translating to 1k in bazaar during the night) in about 1 and a half hours. not tough at all. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361567">Draogan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- 62 Archmage<br>
